  "caption": "Figure 3 Chaseviridae. Partitioned Maximum Likelihood phylogenetic tree of the RNA polymerase and terminase large subunit amino acid sequences of members of the family Chaseviridae . For each predicted protein, amino acid sequences were aligned with MAFFT ( Katoh and Standley 2013 ), and trimmed with Trimal using the setting “gappyout” ( Capella-Gutiérrez et al., 2009 ). The phylogenetic tree was constructed using the IQ-Tree suite, using the partitioned analysis with mixed data setting using as input the full multiple sequence alignment of each protein sequence with ultrafast bootstraps (UFBoot) calculated on 1000 repetitions ( Nguyen et al., 2015 , Chernomor et al., 2016 , Hoang et al., 2018 ). For both genes, the best fitting substitution model was LG+G4 as determined using ModelFinder on each alignment separately, based on the Bayesian Information Criterion ( Kalyaanamoorthy et al., 2017 ). The log-likelihood of the final tree was -18292. The consensus tree was drawn midpoint rooted with unclassified viruses indicated by open circles. UFBoot values above 95% are shown at nodes. This phylogenetic tree and corresponding sequence alignment files are available to download from the Resources page.",
